Domain.Description: Codes to note which categories are associated with different processes.

Values.Value: Water - The water class includes all surface waters: streams, rivers, canals, ponds, reservoirs, lakes, bays, estuaries, and coastal waters.
Impervious Surface - An impervious surface is a landscape feature that prevents or substantially limits rainfall from infiltrating into the soil.
Soil and Barren - The Soil and Barren class includes soil, bare rock, mud, clay and sand.
Trees and Forest - The Trees and Forest class includes trees of any kind, from a single individual to continuous canopy forest.
Shrubland - Shrubs are generally shorter than trees and bear multiple woody stems.
Grass & Herbaceous - The Grass and Herbaceous class includes the gramminoids, forbs and herbs lacking persistent woody stems.
Agriculture - The Agriculture class includes herbaceous vegetation planted or being managed for the production of food, feed, or fiber.
Woody Wetlands - Woody Wetlands are wetlands dominated by Tree and Forest species.
Emergent Wetlands - Emergent Wetlands are wetlands dominated by Grass and Herbaceous species.
